# 🌊 OceanView Resort — Hotel Management System

A full-stack hotel management web application built with **vanilla HTML/CSS/JavaScript** on the frontend and a **pure Java HTTP Server** (no frameworks) on the backend, using **Microsoft SQL Server** for data persistence. Built with Maven and tested with a comprehensive JUnit API test suite.

> **Public Repository:** [https://github.com/faz2001/OceanViewResort](https://github.com/faz2001/OceanViewResort)
> **Report:** [REPORT.md](./REPORT.md)

---

## 📖 Project Overview

OceanView Resort is a multi-user hotel operations platform. Guests can browse rooms and make reservations online; staff members can manage rates, billing, and e-bills; and administrators oversee the full system. The entire backend is powered by a handcrafted Java HTTP server using only the built-in `com.sun.net.httpserver` package — no Spring, no Jakarta EE, no external web frameworks.

---

## ✨ Features

### 👤 Authentication
- User registration and login via `AuthHandler` / `AuthService`
- Session-based access control across all protected endpoints
- Role-aware routing (guest vs. staff vs. admin)

### 🏨 Room Management
- Browse and manage hotel rooms via `RoomHandler`
- Room availability, type descriptions, and pricing display

### 📅 Reservations
- Full reservation lifecycle via `ReservationHandler` / `ReservationService`
- Overlap/conflict detection before confirming bookings
- Guest dashboard showing current and past reservations

### 💳 Billing & E-Bills
- Billing records generated per reservation via `BillingHandler` / `BillingService`
- Electronic bill (e-bill) generation and retrieval via `EBillHandler`
- Itemised invoice data returned as JSON

### 👔 Staff Management
- Staff accounts and records managed via `StaffHandler` / `StaffService`
- Staff-only routes protected by role checks

### 💰 Rate Management
- Room rate configuration via `RateHandler`
- Dynamic pricing support per room type

### 🌐 Frontend (Vanilla JS)
- `index.html` — Public-facing landing / home page
- `OceanView_Public.html` — Public resort information page
- `dashboard.html` — Authenticated user / staff dashboard

### ⚙️ Technical Highlights
- Pure Java `com.sun.net.httpserver.HttpServer` — zero web-framework dependencies
- Maven build system (`pom.xml`) with standard `src/main` / `src/test` layout
- MSSQL JDBC with parameterised queries (SQL injection prevention)
- Hand-rolled `JsonUtil` for building JSON responses without external libraries
- CORS preflight support verified by dedicated test
- 10 JUnit API integration test classes covering all major endpoints
- Two GitHub Actions workflows: Java CI and SLSA3 provenance publishing

